   Installing SearchGuide:
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
   
   Just click on one of the Install icons.
   
   If you don't want to put the full path for SearchGuide in your
   "Search" links, I recommand that you put SearchGuide executable
   in your c: directory. Multiview doesn't seem to inherit the
   path when lanched via a guide's default tool tooltype on
   Workbench...(?)
   

@endnode
@node introduction "Introduction to SearchGuide"
@prev installation

   INTRODUCTION
   ~~~~~~~~~~~~

   SearchGuide is a little search tool for Amigaguide documents.
   
   It is far from perfect, yet, but it does help a bit!
   
   Please note that this version is still a PRE-release, so
   don't hesitate to mail me your suggestions and bug reports.
   
   SearchGuide has been originaly written for Jérôme Chesnot's 
   "France_Guide 2.0".
   
   SearchGuide is localized. If you do a catalog translation for 
   a not yet supported language, please send me a copy of the
   SearchGuide.ct file, I'll then include the resulting catalog 
   with the next release.

   If you use it in your guide(s), please send me an email.


@endnode
