@node history "History"

V0.8.2.3

   Made some changes in the search loop.


V0.8.2.2

   Miscellaneous improvements.


V0.8.2.1

   SearchGuide was sometimes finding things that didn't look like the
   requested keyword. This was due to the use of StrConvert() from 
   locale.library. This function was translating, for example:
   
      "\@{b}are you\@{ub}"  to
      "\@abcare you\@aubc"  
          ^^^  
   So, if you were looking for "car" it would find the
   line containing the above.      
   
   Thanks to Pascal Chiozzi for reporting this "feature" ;-)

   The lines where the keyword has been found are now displayed in 
   their original case, before they were translated to lower case!


V0.8.1.6

   Added new option D=DEFAULT to put a default keyword in the string
   requester. This option is mutually exclusive with the KW=KEYWORD 
   option.
   
   Suggested by Jérôme Chesnot and Gonzalez Rocha.

V0.8.1.5

   Now looks for the following guide viewers, in this order:
   
   The viewer given as argument "VIEWER" if any, otherwise:
      SYS:Utilities/Multiview
      Multiview
      SYS:Utilities/AmigaGuide
      AmigaGuide 
   
   New option KW=KEYWORD, to look for a keyword directly without showing
   the string requester. Suggested by Pascal Chiozzi.
         
   Recompiled with SAS/C 6.57 (plus option OPTIMIZESCHEDULE).

   
V0.8.1.4

   Crash under AmigaOS 2.x fixed.
   
   Spanish catalog included. Thanks to Perez Walls <alu339@csi.ull.es>
   

V0.8.1.3:

   New optional argument VIEWER/K, otherwise default to "SYS:Utilities/Multi-
   view", then "Multiview".

   New optional argument PUBSCREEN/K, used for the feedback window and as 
   argument to the viewer for the resulting found guide, otherwise defaults 
   to the default public screen.
  
   Includes Dutch, French, German, Italian, Norwegian, Polish, Swedish
   locale catalogs. English built-in ;-)
   
   Installation via Installer.
   
   Documentation in AmigaGuide format.

   In found guide, keywords found in the SAME node as the previous one are 
   not separated by a line (separator) anymore. But they still get their 
   proper button: the created link takes into account the node line number.


V0.8.1.2:

   Internal only, not released.
   

V0.8.1.1:

   The "Looking for..." feedback window now open on the default public 
   screen.


V0.8a: 

   SearchGuide didn't put a "}" at the end of its "link" lines. This one 
   didn't show up under Multiview 40.8, Amigaguide DataTypes 40.6, 
   Kickstart 39.106 and WB 40.42. 
   
   Thanks to Jim Hines <hines_j@wvlink.mpl.com> for reporting this big one.


V0.8:

   Builds the found nodes' guide in "T:" instead of the original guide's 
   directory.
   

V0.7:

   Now find bold, hilighted, etc.. text!


V0.6:

   Search routine now "locale" aware (tested only with french, ...and 
   english ;-).

   Includes french, polish and swedish catalogs.
   (english builtin!).
   
@endnode

